{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-post-js","path":"/nubank/credit-card-design","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"html":"<h3 id=\"joining-credit-card\" style=\"position:relative;\">Joining credit card<a href=\"#joining-credit-card\" aria-label=\"joining credit card permalink\" class=\"header-anchor after\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"20\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"20\" fill=\"var(--font-mid-contrast)\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a></h3>\n<p>When I joined Nubank, my interest for human behaviour, business, data models and the dry access to credit in my home country swiftly drew me to focus on Nubank’s core product: the credit card.</p>\n<p>Back then, designers were focused on shipping new products and I was excited to push our core product to the next level.</p>\n<h3 id=\"embracing-leadership\" style=\"position:relative;\">Embracing leadership<a href=\"#embracing-leadership\" aria-label=\"embracing leadership permalink\" class=\"header-anchor after\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"20\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"20\" fill=\"var(--font-mid-contrast)\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a></h3>\n<p>As the company jumped into hypergrowth, I organically leaned towards leadership and was fortunate to help build this team from the ground up.</p>\n<p>Credit card has been my home at Nubank for the past 3 years and the best team of product designers, user researchers and content strategists I have ever worked with.</p>\n<!-- |   |   |\n|---|---|\n|<h5>Diego Vieira, Product Designer</h5>|Amanda Elyss, Product Designer|\n|Mariana Medina, UX Writer|Leticia Ratkiewicz, UX Researcher|\n|Ricardo Perotti, UX Researcher|Williams Oliveira, Product Designer|\n|Rafael Rozendo, Product Designer|Ana Menezes, Product Designer|\n|Andre Mooij, Product Designer|Renato Souza, Product Designer|\n|Amanda Legge, Design Manager - Consumer Lending| | -->\n<p><figure class=\"gatsby-resp-image-figure\" style=\"\">\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 940px; \"\n    >\n      <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 40%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"Credit Card Design team, Dec. 2020\"\n        title=\"Credit Card Design team, Dec. 2020\"\n        src=\"/static/6275301b4e6682ba1c1c9666191c5b7d/7ef15/credit-card-design-team-2.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/6275301b4e6682ba1c1c9666191c5b7d/6c4e6/credit-card-design-team-2.png 235w,\n/static/6275301b4e6682ba1c1c9666191c5b7d/f9c87/credit-card-design-team-2.png 470w,\n/static/6275301b4e6682ba1c1c9666191c5b7d/7ef15/credit-card-design-team-2.png 940w,\n/static/6275301b4e6682ba1c1c9666191c5b7d/77c84/credit-card-design-team-2.png 1410w,\n/static/6275301b4e6682ba1c1c9666191c5b7d/0b3f2/credit-card-design-team-2.png 1607w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 940px) 100vw, 940px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n      />\n    </span>\n    <figcaption class=\"gatsby-resp-image-figcaption\"><p>Credit Card Design team, Dec. 2020</p></figcaption>\n  </figure></p>\n<!-- Iougo Huan, Product Designer -->\n<!-- ### Team Impact -->\n<!-- LT: Early suggestions on how to interview designers (shared with Egon) -->\n<!-- Ana Mê, Rafa, Polyana: Structure our Design Days\nWilliams: loading screen states -->\n<!-- Amanda Elyss: boleto payment + Critique Queen -->\n<!-- Diego and Amanda Legge: Ultravioleta -->\n<!-- Leticia and I: Mapping user needs and product opportunities for the Business Unit + Presenting our process at UXRConf 2020 -->\n<!-- Rafael Rozendo: Secured Lines/Card -->\n<!-- Andre Mooij: Launching México\nAna Mê: Collecting debt -->\n<h3 id=\"impact\" style=\"position:relative;\">Impact<a href=\"#impact\" aria-label=\"impact permalink\" class=\"header-anchor after\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"20\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"20\" fill=\"var(--font-mid-contrast)\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a></h3>\n<p>Our main accomplishments have been to:</p>\n<div style=\"display:flex-center; margin-top:1rem;\"> \n\t<div style=\"background-color:var(--bg-light); padding: 16px; border-radius:3px;margin:0 0 16px 0 ;flex-grow: 1;width: auto;\">\n\t\t<h3 style=\"margin-top:0\"><strong>1</strong></h3>\n        <h3 style=\"margin-top:0\"><strong>Build and nurture a strong design team</strong></h3>\n\t\t<p>Always ready to help each other grow in their careers</p>\n\t</div>\n    <div style=\"background-color:var(--bg-light); padding: 16px; border-radius:3px;margin:0 0 16px 0 ;flex-grow: 1;width: auto;\">\n\t\t<h3 style=\"margin-top:0\"><strong>2</strong></h3>\n        <h3 style=\"margin-top:0\"><strong>Outline our vision of the future</strong></h3>\n\t\t<p>Keeping Brazilians' favourite credit card always fresh and meaningful to them</p>\n\t</div>\n    <div style=\"background-color:var(--bg-light); padding: 16px; border-radius:3px;margin:0 8px 0 0 ;flex-grow: 1;width: auto; margin: auto\">\n\t\t<h3 style=\"margin-top:0\"><strong>3</strong></h3>\n        <h3 style=\"margin-top:0\"><strong>Nurture a trusting and collaborative environment</strong></h3>\n\t\t<p>For both designers and our cross-functional partners.</p>\n\t</div>\n\t<div style=\"background-color:var(--bg-lightest); padding: 16px; border-radius:3px;margin:0 0 0 8px;flex-grow: 1; width: calc(50% - 8px)\">\n\t</div>\n</div>\n<br>\n<p>Let’s dive into each of these areas and some of the work done behind each of them. As with any great band, these were a group effort and not my accomplish alone.</p>\n<p>I’m proud of how we optimised our team for autonomy and collaboration, making this is a collective story of success. I’ll try to cover the surface, but if you’d like to learn more about any of these, feel free to <a href=\"mailto:hey@lucasterra.com?subject=Building a Design Team\">reach me</a>.</p>\n<hr>\n<h2 id=\"1-build-and-nurture-a-strong-team\" style=\"position:relative;\">1. Build and nurture a strong team<a href=\"#1-build-and-nurture-a-strong-team\" aria-label=\"1 build and nurture a strong team permalink\" class=\"header-anchor after\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"20\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"20\" fill=\"var(--font-mid-contrast)\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a></h2>\n<p><figure class=\"gatsby-resp-image-figure\" style=\"\">\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 940px; \"\n    >\n      <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 74.8936170212766%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"A daily sync from the early days of our team · with Diego, Leticia and Egon\"\n        title=\"A daily sync from the early days of our team · with Diego, Leticia and Egon\"\n        src=\"/static/4130ac7d9208d3a5e055fbc1d4c595ef/f06fb/Daily-sync-from-when-we-were-a-small-team.jpg\"\n        srcset=\"/static/4130ac7d9208d3a5e055fbc1d4c595ef/5d189/Daily-sync-from-when-we-were-a-small-team.jpg 235w,\n/static/4130ac7d9208d3a5e055fbc1d4c595ef/7d6cd/Daily-sync-from-when-we-were-a-small-team.jpg 470w,\n/static/4130ac7d9208d3a5e055fbc1d4c595ef/f06fb/Daily-sync-from-when-we-were-a-small-team.jpg 940w,\n/static/4130ac7d9208d3a5e055fbc1d4c595ef/c75e4/Daily-sync-from-when-we-were-a-small-team.jpg 1410w,\n/static/4130ac7d9208d3a5e055fbc1d4c595ef/0dd9a/Daily-sync-from-when-we-were-a-small-team.jpg 1880w,\n/static/4130ac7d9208d3a5e055fbc1d4c595ef/05366/Daily-sync-from-when-we-were-a-small-team.jpg 3264w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 940px) 100vw, 940px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n      />\n    </span>\n    <figcaption class=\"gatsby-resp-image-figcaption\"><p>A daily sync from the early days of our team · with Diego, Leticia and Egon</p></figcaption>\n  </figure></p>\n<h3 id=\"finding-the-right-people\" style=\"position:relative;\">Finding the right people<a href=\"#finding-the-right-people\" aria-label=\"finding the right people permalink\" class=\"header-anchor after\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"20\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"20\" fill=\"var(--font-mid-contrast)\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a></h3>\n<p>In 2018, Nubank hit puberty and was starting to grow fast. As with any adolescent, different parts of the body grew faster than others and Design was one that took longer to develop.</p>\n<p>The first three people I helped hire (in the picture above) had a complementary set of personalities, backgrounds and technical skills. We used that in our favour so that our skills and interests would match different parts of the user journey people had with their credit cards. Diego, for example has deep apreciation for details and has been leading design for our rewards program for the past couple of years. </p>\n<p>A few months in and it was now their time to also help find the best talent our there, so I shared my thoughts and learnings from interviewing design candidates.</p>\n<img src=\"\" alt=\"Personal notes on hiring, shared with early members of the team\">\n<p><figure class=\"gatsby-resp-image-figure\" style=\"\">\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 940px; \"\n    >\n      <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 74.8936170212766%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"Co-designing a better UI for the transaction feed · with Amanda, Diego, Ana\"\n        title=\"Co-designing a better UI for the transaction feed · with Amanda, Diego, Ana\"\n        src=\"/static/7932cfdd05fc408a06613fedc275aad5/f06fb/co--design.jpg\"\n        srcset=\"/static/7932cfdd05fc408a06613fedc275aad5/5d189/co--design.jpg 235w,\n/static/7932cfdd05fc408a06613fedc275aad5/7d6cd/co--design.jpg 470w,\n/static/7932cfdd05fc408a06613fedc275aad5/f06fb/co--design.jpg 940w,\n/static/7932cfdd05fc408a06613fedc275aad5/c75e4/co--design.jpg 1410w,\n/static/7932cfdd05fc408a06613fedc275aad5/0dd9a/co--design.jpg 1880w,\n/static/7932cfdd05fc408a06613fedc275aad5/f8b09/co--design.jpg 4032w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 940px) 100vw, 940px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n      />\n    </span>\n    <figcaption class=\"gatsby-resp-image-figcaption\"><p>Co-designing a better UI for the transaction feed · with Amanda, Diego, Ana</p></figcaption>\n  </figure></p>\n<h3 id=\"evolving-our-rituals\" style=\"position:relative;\">Evolving our rituals<a href=\"#evolving-our-rituals\" aria-label=\"evolving our rituals permalink\" class=\"header-anchor after\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"20\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"20\" fill=\"var(--font-mid-contrast)\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a></h3>\n<p>Fastforward to when the team had doubled in size (around 6 people) and our rituals had evolved a ton. We also started sharing some of the housekeeping tasks so everybody was a leader in one direction. Diego and Ana, for example took over our team retrospectives and Elyss was nominated our design critique queen, helping team members ensure they were making the most out of their design crits.</p>\n<img src=\"\" alt=\"Design Day agenda · by Ana, Poly and Rafa\">\n<h3 id=\"working-as-a-remote-team\" style=\"position:relative;\">Working as a remote team<a href=\"#working-as-a-remote-team\" aria-label=\"working as a remote team permalink\" class=\"header-anchor after\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"20\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"20\" fill=\"var(--font-mid-contrast)\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a></h3>\n<p>More recently, during the pandemic we all struggled with calendar tetris, making space for collaboration and getting to know the new people joining the team. Ana, Rafa and Poly then organized an online “Design Studio Day” block on Thursdays so that we always have time in the week to focus in our work, gather feedback, learn more about what others are working on and get to know one another.</p>\n<p>It takes time to make a team work, and even more time to make it work out. The integration an collaboration that comes with spending Thursdays together as a team has really paid off on the long-run.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Supporting each other on the development of our careers, by Leticia and I at UXR conf</li>\n</ul>\n<hr>\n<h2 id=\"2-setting-the-vision\" style=\"position:relative;\">2. Setting the vision<a href=\"#2-setting-the-vision\" aria-label=\"2 setting the vision permalink\" class=\"header-anchor after\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"20\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"20\" fill=\"var(--font-mid-contrast)\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a></h2>\n<p>From early 2018 until early 2019 the design and product teams were so focused on the day-to-day that we barely had the means to think of the next semester (also because our customer base would suffer drastic shifts). In 2019, we started having weekly working sessions involving Product Designers, Product Managers, Product Marketing and UX Researchers.</p>\n<p>These meetings took different shapes over the years but were important to give everyone in the room visibility about what was happening to the product and also be able to connect the different moving pieces. These sessions played a big role and open space for looking ahead into the future.</p>\n<p>While our current vision of the future will always be confidential, here are some of the bits that are pushing us into that direction.</p>\n<h3 id=\"being-more-thoughtful-about-what-once-were-edge-cases\" style=\"position:relative;\">Being more thoughtful about what once were “edge cases”<a href=\"#being-more-thoughtful-about-what-once-were-edge-cases\" aria-label=\"being more thoughtful about what once were edge cases permalink\" class=\"header-anchor after\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"20\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"20\" fill=\"var(--font-mid-contrast)\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a></h3>\n<img src=\"\">\n<h3 id=\"being-more-adaptable-to-our-customers-needs-pandemic\" style=\"position:relative;\">Being more adaptable to our customers needs (pandemic)<a href=\"#being-more-adaptable-to-our-customers-needs-pandemic\" aria-label=\"being more adaptable to our customers needs pandemic permalink\" class=\"header-anchor after\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"20\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"20\" fill=\"var(--font-mid-contrast)\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a></h3>\n<p>The world has changed drastically over the past 5 years. Mobile payments grew exponentially, Brazilians stopped paying fees for credit cards, the pandemic crisis made over X/Y brazilians loose their jobs. Over the year of 2020, we have worked on a number of initiatives that helped our customers get to the other side together. </p>\n<h3 id=\"expanding-into-new-geographies\" style=\"position:relative;\">Expanding into new geographies<a href=\"#expanding-into-new-geographies\" aria-label=\"expanding into new geographies permalink\" class=\"header-anchor after\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"20\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"20\" fill=\"var(--font-mid-contrast)\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a></h3>\n<ul>\n<li>Launching Mexico, by Andre Mooij\n– Launching Colombia, by Santiago Eastmann</li>\n</ul>\n<h3 id=\"preparing-the-path-for-the-next-50mm-customers\" style=\"position:relative;\">Preparing the path for the next 50MM customers<a href=\"#preparing-the-path-for-the-next-50mm-customers\" aria-label=\"preparing the path for the next 50mm customers permalink\" class=\"header-anchor after\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"20\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"20\" fill=\"var(--font-mid-contrast)\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a></h3>\n<ul>\n<li></li>\n</ul>\n<h3 id=\"hitting-refresh-in-our-rewards-program\" style=\"position:relative;\">Hitting refresh in our rewards program<a href=\"#hitting-refresh-in-our-rewards-program\" aria-label=\"hitting refresh in our rewards program permalink\" class=\"header-anchor after\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"20\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"20\" fill=\"var(--font-mid-contrast)\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a></h3>\n<ul>\n<li>New ways for a credit card to work on, led by Amanda Elyss</li>\n<li>Recover the magic by solving what were once “edge cases”, led by both Ana Mê Collections and Will in Limits</li>\n<li>Building a path to credit for the next 25MM customers, led by myself and Rafa Rozendo</li>\n<li>Ultravioleta, led by Amanda Legge and Diego Vieira</li>\n</ul>\n<h2 id=\"3-fostering-trust-and-collaboration\" style=\"position:relative;\">3. Fostering trust and collaboration<a href=\"#3-fostering-trust-and-collaboration\" aria-label=\"3 fostering trust and collaboration permalink\" class=\"header-anchor after\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"20\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"20\" fill=\"var(--font-mid-contrast)\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a></h2>\n<p>Trust is the seed for any autonomous and collaborative team. I feel like I’ve been lucky to work with people who I cou</p>\n<p>Within our design team, there are a couple of rituals that </p>\n<ol>\n<li>Creative sessions are a reserved space of the week where designers can decide to run a design critique, a team discussion, </li>\n<li>Team retros are for oiling up the engines. They’re usually facilitated by Diego, who also excells at designing spreadsheets such as this one</li>\n<li>Internal peers: critiques with Amanda Elyss and retros with Diego </li>\n<li>External peers: collaborating on presentations, helping create a product review forum for the Credit Card, Lending and Collections teams</li>\n</ol>\n<p>———</p>\n<p>Things people told me that kept me engaged building this product and team:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>You have been invaluable at onboarding PMs in Credit Card\n<br>— Mariana Penido, Head of Product for Credit Card</p>\n</blockquote>\n<blockquote>\n<p>The credit card business unit is the most innovative at Nubank. Not because you’re launching new products all the time, but because you’ve been successful at constantly questioning what has been true/ great in the past <br> — Renata Veiga, Design Manager for Lending products</p>\n</blockquote>\n<blockquote>\n<p>To me it’s 100% clear Lucas doesn’t work for the Credit Card business unit — nor for Nubank — but for our customers. And he knows how to go all the way back to tell how these decisions have an impact on the business\n<br>— Luiza Ferraz, Product Marketing Manager</p>\n</blockquote>\n<hr>\n<h3 id=\"what-clients-have-said-about-our-work\" style=\"position:relative;\">What clients have said about our work<a href=\"#what-clients-have-said-about-our-work\" aria-label=\"what clients have said about our work permalink\" class=\"header-anchor after\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"20\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"20\" fill=\"var(--font-mid-contrast)\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a></h3>","frontmatter":{"path":"/nubank/credit-card-design","date":"2018 - now","lastEdit":null,"featuredImage":null,"role":"aaa","accent":"var(--bg-lightest)","color":"","title":"Designing a Design Team","subtitle":"Building and leading Nubank's credit card design team","designteam":null,"topics":null,"published":null,"impact":null,"company":"Nubank","location":"São Paulo, Brazil","icon":null}}},"pageContext":{}},"staticQueryHashes":["3649515864","63159454"]}